thread.title: Video: Halesowen Town 1 Ashton United 2

title: Video: Halesowen Town 1 Ashton United 2
text:
Tweet 
The Yeltz failed to produce the hoped for reaction to last Tuesday’s 6-0 defeat in a disappointing display. 
But hey still grabbed the lead in first-half injury time, when Danny Bragoli headed home directly from a well weighted corner from Aaron Griffiths. 
The lead slipped away after the interval as the ever-sharp Martin Pilkington nipped in to stab Ashton’s 56th minute equaliser into an empty net. 
He caught out defender Rob Elvins and goalkeeper Matt Sargeant to a long ball straight down the centre. 
Joe Hull fired narrowly wide for Halesowen, but the Robins broke straight up the field. More on this story:
